<item>
  <title>Why Jaxon Smith-Njigba is the most efficient WR in the NFL</title>
  <dc:creator>Ben Ofe</dc:creator>
  <link>https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/why-jsn-is-the-most-efficient-wide-receiver-in-the-nfl/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>High-volume receivers in the NFL aren’t usually the most efficient when it comes to it. Throw a guy the ball 150 times he is obviously going to put up some numbers. It’s about what they do with it once they catch the ball. Players like Justin Jefferson, DK Metcalf, and Courtland Sutton struggled this season to be efficient at high volume.</p>
<p>That was the exact opposite story for Jaxon Smith-Njigba. He wasn’t the highest volume receiver in the NFL, but nobody came close to what he could do with once he got the ball. JSN also wasn’t just the NFL receiving yards leader but the most efficient wideout this past season of the National Football League.</p>
