<p>Now this is where JSN excels and does his dirty work here. The green dot is yards per target that shows the yardage of a ball thrown the way caught or not, and the navy dot is what he averages when he makes a catch. You can see on this dumbbell chart that Smith-Njigba leads in the NFL with his 15.1 yards per reception in this stat by a WIDE margin. Before he even catches the ball, you can see that he almost already has all-pro guys like Jamar Chase and Chris Olave beat with what they do on each reception. This is largely in part due to his ability to take the short and medium yardage catches and get upfield to turn them into something more.</p>
<p>The common denominator that comes up here in every chart is that JSN accomplishes more with less than other receivers in the NFL. He catches everything that Sam Darnold throws his way, plays with a ton of efficiency, and makes things happen after the catch. That’s exactly what makes him the most effective wide receiver.</p>



